<section class="materials-content-section">
  <div class="container">
    <div style="max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto; margin-bottom: 4rem;">
      <h2>Quality Materials Ensure Decades of Durability</h2>
      <p>A modular kitchen or wardrobe is a long-term investment. While carpenter-made products often use low-grade commercial plywood or particle board that swells in humid conditions, BVN Modulars guarantees high-performance materials in all packages. Here is our breakdown of the materials we use.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="materials-grid">
      <div class="material-card">
        <h3>1. Plywood & Board Selection</h3>
        <p>We use Boiling Water Proof (BWP) and Boiling Water Resistant (BWR) marine plywood for wet areas (kitchens and bathroom units) and commercial-grade IS:303 plywood for dry areas (wardrobes, TV cabinets, and desks).</p>
        <ul style="margin-top: 1rem;">
          <li>BWP Plywood: 100% waterproof, survives boiling water for 72 hours.</li>
          <li>Calibrated Plywood: Uniform thickness, crucial for CNC precision.</li>
          <li>Zero gaps: Internally layered without hollow pockets.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="material-card">
        <h3>2. Premium Laminate Finishes</h3>
        <p>Our sheets are hot-pressed at the factory using heavy machinery, eliminating the bubbles and peel-offs common with carpenter hand-gluing. We offer a catalogue of over 100 finishes.</p>
        <ul style="margin-top: 1rem;">
          <li>High-Gloss Acrylic: Mirror-like reflectiveness, ideal for kitchens.</li>
          <li>Matte & Textured: Modern, smudge-resistant, easy to clean.</li>
          <li>Brands: Greenlam, CenturyLaminates, Merino, and Virgo.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="material-card">
        <h3>3. Smooth Soft-Close Hardware</h3>
        <p>Fittings undergo thousands of cycles. We use premium certified hardware brands that come with long warranties to ensure smooth cabinet opening for years.</p>
        <ul style="margin-top: 1rem;">
          <li>Soft-close Hinges: Zero door slamming noise.</li>
          <li>Tandem Boxes: Smooth drawer sliding under high weights.</li>
          <li>Brands: Hettich, Hafele, and Blum hardware.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div style="margin-top: 5rem; text-align: center; background-color: var(--bg-offwhite); padding: 3rem; border-radius: 6px; box-shadow: var(--shadow-light);">
